I'm not so sure the "changes" are going to be THAT devistating considering the feedback from monks on Test. Sure we will get hit harder when we do get hit, but according to a number of monks on Test, they were getting hit less often. So less hits at a higher damage can = about the same as more hits for less damage. The funny thing is, mobs that are mid 60's that hit for 300+ anyhow will STILL hit for 300+ (regardless of your AC they hit for darn near full damage most of the time anyway) just now you'll have a better chance to avoid more of those hits. Soloing is a tossup depending on what your killing, but for the most part the mobs I solo dont have a high melee damage and spend the majority of their time trying to slow me or nuke me. (And since i'm wearing my resist gear when fighting them and have a bard for backup resists, I rarely get slowed or nuked.) Quite simply this COULD very well be a GOOD thing for Monks in general. Now if they fudged with my total hitpoints, i'd have to flying kick someone in the head for that! <p>Brother Lizzik : 60 Monk : Grandmaster with Turbo Fists!
